<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1862-12-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1862-12-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="17" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d17">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 429.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1862-12-20"><hi rend="italic">December</hi> 20, 1862.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I herewith enclose, for presentation to
                            the British government, a copy of memorials and other papers addressed
                            to the President of the United States by several ship-owners, resident
                            within the collection district of New Bedford, Massachusetts, relative
                            to the capture and destruction of the American whaling vessels, the
                            Virginia, the Benjamin Tucker, the Elisha Dunbar, the Ocean Rover, the
                            Altamaha, and the Ocmulgee, by the piratical steamer Alabama, in the
                            month of September last.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>